column2: Light haze- lt. ripple- algae bloom- 7.52" rain 8/17-9/5.
Clear- slight ripple- and algal bloom around shore.  There was 7.62" of rain from 8/17-9/10.
Sunny- clear- algae bloom- and a very slight ripple.  The rain gauge reading from 9/10-9/26 was 1.8"
Heavy ripple- partly cloudy at start of test- then started raining mid way through tests- very little rain though.  The rain gauge from 9/26-10/20 is 2.6".
Pieces of algae size of peas throughout water. Lake approximately 1' over normal. Medium ripple. Hazy day.
Northwest wind at 5-10 mph- partly cloudy- NE shore sprayed 7/12 with cuso4
Cloudy- S wind- light ripple- lake sprayed w/cuso4 on 7/27- depth: 23'
Clear- SW wind at 10 mph- lake sprayed w/cuso4 on 8/9 and 8/16- deepest spot: 22'.  Rain gauge reading from 7/25-8/21 is 3.15 inches.
Northwest wind- medium ripple- mostly cloudy- depth: 22'.  Rain gauge reading from 8/23-9/23 is 10.45 inches.
Light northwest wind and clear.  Rainfall is 1.1" between 9/23-10/21.
Partly cloudy. Very light ripple. Slimy green starting to grow fast on bottom. Water has heavy green dots
Medium ripple. Partly cloudy. Some green dots throughout water. Staff gauge installed 6/2.
Heavy ripple. Partly cloudy. Some green dots in water.
Light ripple and overcast.  Light amount of algae.
Clear. Sunny. Heavy ripple. NW wind.  Rain gauge reading from 4/19-8/10 is 14.35 inches.  April had 3.2"- May had 1.4"- June had 1.75"- July had 5.7"- and August had 2.3".
Mostly cloudy- hazy- medium ripple.  Rain gauge reading from 8/11-9/15 is 3.9 inches.  There was 2.55 inches in august and 1.35 inches in September.
Light ripple- partly cloudy- clumps of algae floating on top of the water.  Rain gauge reading from 9/15-10/13 is 3.0 inches.
Partly cloudy. Medium ripple. 10-15 mph winds.
Partly cloudy- medium ripple- lake is extremely green- lake level is much higher than in recent years. 9.65" rain from 5/25/93 - 7/9/93
Light ripple- very few clouds.  Blue green algae from shore as far as 60' out from shore.  Looks like paint pots in Yellowstone.
Clear. very small ripple.  Water looked like pea soup from shore out as far as 60'.  Some blue-green algae on shoreline.
Medium ripple partly cloudy- blue-green algae close to shore.
Clear- medium ripple.  Green blue algae in spots along the shore.
Clear sky- medium ripple from approximately- 10 mph winds- light amount of algae near shore wind blowing into.
Partly cloudy- mild ripple- algae and some blue green- algae near the shore.
Light to moderate wind- hazy.  Light ripple.
Very hazy.  Light ripple- very hazy.
Northwest wind 5-10 mph- clear sky- no algae- lots of weeds.
Heavy algae on NE shoreline- partly cloudy.  Light ripple.
Very light wind and ripple- very minor algae particles in the water- clear sky
Very light wind.  Partly cloudy.  Water always seems to have a brownish cast to it.  No algae.
Light ripple- partly cloudy.  Some brown globs floating in water.
Light wind-partly cloudy.  Green scum along shoreline.
Mild ripple- partly cloudy- large clumps of what appears to be pollen- cottonwood fuzz- poplar fuzz and dandelion fuzz along the lakeshore.
Lake level on 6/5 was 95.38.  Very calm-sunny-yellow green scum along shoreline.  Possible pollen-cottonwood-poplar-dandelions and algae.
Yellow- green scum along the shoreline and in the weeds- light overcast- approx. 10 mph wind.
Very light ripple- overcast- lots of algae along the shoreline.
Partly cloudy- 15 mph wind- algae along shoreline.
Clear sky and lake. SW wind 5 mph.
Very very light NE wind. Partly cloudy. Some greenish brown debris floating near surface.
Very very light wind- partly cloudy- approx. 85 degrees F- perfect day.
Very light winds- northeast- few clouds- a very beautiful day.
Very light wind- mostly sunny- temp is approximately 50 degrees.

No wind- very few clouds.  Lake level lower than normal for this time of year.  Only 4 inches of rain from 4/5/97 to present.
Light breeze- light ripple.  Partly cloudy.  Rain gauge reading from 6/12/97 to 7/28/97 = 7.8 inches.
No wind.  Very few clouds.  Very slight amounts of algae in the water.  Rain gauge reading from7/28/97 to 8/28/97=3.0 inches.
Some algae around the shoreline.  Windy 10-15 mph. A few clouds. Rain gauge reading from 8/29/97 to 9/16/97=4.8 inches.
Very light wind.  Very few clouds.  Rain gauge reading from 9/17/97 to 10/16/97 = 1.8 inches.
Kind of murky- partly cloudy- NW wind- 5-10 mph 80 F.
Cloudy- rained- south-southwest wind 15 mph- 67 F- lot of weeds.
Lake is very green- partly cloudy- west wind 10-15 mph- 53 F chilly.
Lake is green- clear + sunny- eagles + gulls- 60 F.
